Take the @butter{8%tsp} out of the fridge, bringing to room temperature. Preheat the #oven{} to 200 degrees. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @yellow onion{2}(thinly sliced). Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the sliced onions and cook, tossing, until slightly caramelized for ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{2%tbsp} and cook for another ~{5%minutes} until jammy. Remove from the pan and set aside.

While the onions cook, core and thinly slice the @pear{2}(thinly sliced). Tear the @boston lettuce{2}(torn into large bite-sized pieces) into large bite-sized pieces, discarding the core.

Spread two slices of @whole wheat bread{8%slices} with 1 teaspoon butter each. On a #cutting board{}, lay the slices butter-side down. Top one slice with 1/4 of the caramelized onions, @Gruyère cheese{8%oz}, and pear slices (reserving some for the salad). Spread the other slice of bread with 1/2 teaspoon @Dijon mustard{1%unit}. Place it on top of the other slice, butter-side up. Repeat this process for the remaining sandwiches.

Wash out the pan you used for the onions and heat it over medium-low. Working in batches, place the sandwiches in the pan and cook, for ~{3-5%minutes} per side, until golden brown and the gruyere has melted. Place the finished sandwiches in the oven to keep warm until the entire meal is ready.

== Dressing ==

While the sandwiches cook, whisk together @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, the remaining @balsamic vinegar{2%tbsp}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Cut the sandwiches in half. Toss the lettuce and remaining pear slices with enough dressing to coat. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Serve the pear salad alongside the grilled cheese sandwiches and enjoy!